   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The emergency power off (EPO) is wired as normally open (NO)
to the dry contacts <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b> on the controller.</p>
         <sl class="- topic/sl ">
            <sli class="- topic/sli ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A) </b>Digital input 8.</sli>
            <sli class="- topic/sli ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B) </b>The internal 24 V DC power supply.</sli>
         </sl>
         <p class="- topic/p ">If the circuit is closed the EPO signal is sent to the controller.
The EPO signal trips the output breaker and the load is no longer
supplied by the system.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">For more information see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Drawings</i>.</p>
